ata, from Dun by Nina Jones ac174.jpg|Young shoots of Rata, from Dun\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{Wikicommons|Category:Nina Lucy Mary Jones|Nina Jones}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jones, Nina}}\n[[Category:1871 births]]\n[[Category:1926 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Christchurch]]\n[[Category:Botanical illustrators]]\n[[Category:20th-century New Zealand painters]]\n[[Category:19th-century New Zealand painters]]\n[[Category:Women watercolorists]]\n[[Category:Landscape painters]]\n[[Category:People from Nelson, New Zealand]]\n[[Category:New Zealand women illustrators]]\n[[Category:20th-century New Zealand artists]]\n[[Category:19th-century New Zealand artists]]\n[[Category:19th-century New Zealand women artists]]\n[[Category:20th-century New Zealand women artists]]\n[[Category:Burials at Richmond Cemetery, New Zealand]]\n", "name_user": "Schwede66", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography:spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nina_Jones"}
{"title_page": "Adrian Cheng", "text_new": "{{short description|Hong Kong businessman}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Adrian Cheng<br />\u912d\u5fd7\u525b\n| birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1979}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hong Kong]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Harvard University]]\n| occupation         = Businessman\n| years_active       = 2000s-present\n| known_for          = Founder of [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] and [[K11 Art Foundation]]\n| title              = Executive Vice-Chairman and General Manager of [[New World Development]]\n| term               = 2015-present\n| awards             = [[Officier de l\u2019Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hongkong.consulfrance.org/Mr-Adrian-Cheng-awarded-insignia-of-Officer-in-the-Order-of-Arts-and-Letters|title=Mr. Adrian Cheng awarded insignia of Officer in the Order of Arts and Letters|last=|first=|date=2017-12-12|website=Consulate general of France in Hong Kong and Macau|access-date=2018-01-03}}</ref><br/>Honorary Doctorate of Humanities degree, [[Savannah College of Art and Design|SCAD]]<br />Honorary Fellowship, [[Lingnan University (Hong Kong)|Lingnan University]]\n|module={{Chinese |child=yes |t=\u912d\u5fd7\u525b|s=\u90d1\u5fd7\u521a|j=zeng6 zi3 gong1|p=Zh\u00e8ng Zh\u00ecg\u0101ng}}\n}}\n'''Adrian Cheng Chi-kong''' ({{zh|t=\u912d\u5fd7\u525b}}, born 1979) is a [[Hong Kong]] businessman.<ref name=NextShark1_2017>{{cite news |last=General |first=Ryan |date=February 20, 2017 |title=Meet the Harvard Graduate Who\u2019s Heir to the World\u2019s Biggest Jewelry Empire |trans-title= |url=https://nextshark.com/adrian-cheng-chow-tai-fook/ |language=English |work=NextShark |location=  |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Reuters1_2013>{{cite news |last=Master |first=Farah |date=May 13, 2013 |title=Adrian Cheng: updating a Hong Kong family empire for a changing China |trans-title= |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-chowtaifook-cheng-idUSBRE94C0ZH20130513 |language=English |work=[[Reuters]] |location=  |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=BusinessofFashion_2017>{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng Launches C Ventures, an \u2018Investment Club\u2019 With Eye on Youth Culture |url = https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/news-bites/adrian-cheng-launches-c-ventures-an-investment-club-with-eye-on-youth-culture |website = Business of Fashion}}</ref> He is the executive vice-chairman and general manager of the Hong Kong-listed [[New World Development]],<ref name=NWD_2015>{{Cite web|title = Corporate {{!}} New World Development Company Limited Official Website|url = http://www.nwd.com.hk/corporate|website = www.nwd.com.hk|accessdate = 8 October 2015}}</ref> executive director of jewellery company [[Chow Tai Fook]], and founder of the [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] brand.<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\">{{Cite web|url=http://corporate.chowtaifook.com/en/about/board.php|title=About Us > Board of Directors {{!}} Chow Tai Fook Jewellery Group Limited|website=corporate.chowtaifook.com|access-date=2016-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520145306/http://corporate.chowtaifook.com/en/about/board.php|archive-date=2016-05-20|url-status=dead|df=}}</ref><ref name=SCMP1_2015/><ref name=AsiaTatler1_2018>{{Cite web|title = 5 Things To Know About Victoria Dockside |url = https://hk.asiatatler.com/life/5-things-to-know-about-victoria-dockside |website = Asia Tatler}}</ref> Cheng has been on the [[40 under 40 (Fortune magazine)|40 under 40 list by ''Fortune'']], and in 2017, he was awarded the [[Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]].<ref name=CoboSocial1_2017>{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng Awarded Officier de L\u2019Ordre des Arts et des Lettres |url = https://www.cobosocial.com/dossiers/adrian-cheng-awarded-officier-de-lordre-des-arts-et-des-lettres/ |website = Cobosocial}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nCheng was born in 1979.<ref name=Reuters1_2013/> He is the oldest child of [[Henry Cheng]],<ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> and among his siblings are businesswoman Sonia Cheng<ref name=AsiaTatler1_2018/> and Brian Cheng.<ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> Cheng is the designated heir to his grandfather [[Cheng Yu-tung]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng moves up after K11 artistry - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=11&art_id=154796&sid=43996793&con_type=1&d_str=20150303&fc=2|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150908231034/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=11|archive-date = 2015-09-08|url-status=dead|df = }}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Adrian Chi-Kong Cheng {{!}} #BoF500 {{!}} The Business of Fashion|url = http://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/adrian-chi-kong-cheng|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref> a multi-billionaire<ref name=Coconuts1_2016>[http://hongkong.coconuts.co/2016/09/30/hong-kong-billionaire-tycoon-cheng-yu-tung-dies-aged-91 Hong Kong billionaire tycoon Cheng Yu-tung dies aged 91], Coconuts, 30 September 2016</ref> known for founding [[New World Development]] and [[Chow Tai Fook Enterprises]],<ref name=NextShark1_2017/><ref name=Reuters1_2013/><ref name=BusinessofFashion_2017/> both Cheng family holdings.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|title = Still in Control, Hong Kong Property Tycoons Face a Younger Generation|url = https://www.cnbc.com/id/44899567|accessdate = 2015-09-30|first = Alex Frew McMillan{{!}}CNBC|last = Contributor}}</ref> Cheng majored in East Asian studies at [[Harvard University]] and graduated with a Bachelor of Arts degree.  Cheng's father had established the New World Harvard Kennedy School Fellows Programme in an agreement with Harvard in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www4.hku.hk/hongrads/index.php/archive/graduate_detail/314|title=Honorary Degrees Congregation|website=University of Hong Kong|access-date=6 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=New World Group and the State Administration of Foreign Experts Affairs renewed the agreement for \"New World Harvard Kennedy School Fellows Programme\"|url=https://www.nwd.com.hk/content/new-world-group-and-state-administration-foreign-experts-affairs-renewed-agreement-new-world|website=New World Development Co. Ltd|access-date=6 February 2019}}</ref>  Cheng later went to [[Japan]] to study [[Japanese culture]] for a year.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Business career ==\n=== UBS and Chow Tai Fook ===\nEarly in his career, Cheng was a banker at [[Goldman Sachs]] and [[UBS]].<ref name=Reuters1_2013/> Following a two-year stint at UBS AG,<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" /> in 2006,<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/> Cheng joined the family business,<ref name=\":3\" /> the private Chow Tai Fook Holdings empire.<ref name=\":0\" /> He became executive director of the listed<ref name=\":3\"/> Chow Tai Fook<ref name=SCMP1_2015/> Jewelry Group.<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\"/>\n\n===New World Development===\nIn March 2007, Cheng became the executive director<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/> and a board member at New World Development,<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> a Hong Kong-listed company<ref name=NWD_2015/> which is the biggest part of Chow Tai Fook Holdings.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013>{{Cite news|title = Adrian Cheng adds shine to Chow Tai Fook brand|url = http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/424863ca-d33a-11e2-95d4-00144feab7de.html#slide0|newspaper = Financial Times|date = 2013-10-08|access-date = 2015-09-30|issn = 0307-1766|first = Paul J.|last = Davies}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Brave new world as Cheng retires - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?art_id=120262&con_type=1|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Reflections of Siem - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?art_id=143664&con_type=3|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = New World founder makes way for son at top of developer|url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/29/newworld-management-idUSL4E8DT2EL20120229|newspaper = Reuters|date = 2012-02-29|access-date = 2015-09-30}}</ref> In 2012, he became joint [[general manager]] of New World Development<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/> and he also became executive vice-chairman in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nwd.com.hk/content/adrian-cheng-promoted-nwd-executive-vice-chairman|title=Home {{!}} New World Development Company Limited Official Website|website=www.nwd.com.hk|access-date=2016-05-17}}</ref>\n\n===K11 brand===\nCheng introduced the concept of \"museum-retail\"<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/f5dc36ee-5851-11e4-a31b-00144feab7de.html|title=Arts interview: Adrian Cheng|last=Harris|first=Gareth|date=2014-10-24|newspaper=Financial Times|issn=0307-1766|access-date=2016-05-17}}</ref> by founding the [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] brand in 2008. Cheng's first K11 museum-retail mall opened in [[Tsim Sha Tsui]] (Hong Kong) in 2009, and later a branch was opened in [[K11 (Shanghai)|Shanghai]]. K11 museum-retail shopping centers currently have branches in [[Guangzhou]], Hong Kong, Shanghai, [[Shenyang]], and [[Wuhan]].<ref name=Mingtiandi1_2018/><ref name=CNN1_2018/>\n\n===K11 Art Foundation===\nHe founded the [[K11 Art Foundation]] (KAF) in 2010, a vehicle for art promotion within the malls, serving as a platform for Chinese artists and their works.<ref>{{Cite web|title = The Foundation - K11 Art Foundation|url = http://www.k11artfoundation.org/en/about-us/|accessdate = 2015-09-09}}</ref>  He initiated collaborations between the foundation and international museums and art institutions such as [[Palais de Tokyo]] in [[Paris]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.artnet.com/art-world/k11-art-foundations-chinese-french-connection-at-fiac-143086|title=K11 Art Foundation's Chinese-French Connection at FIAC - artnet News|website=artnet News|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref> and [[Institute of Contemporary Arts]] (ICA) in London,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ica.org.uk/whats-on/seasons/ica-and-k11-art-foundation-present-zhang-ding-enter-dragon|title=ICA and K11 Art Foundation present Zhang Ding: Enter the Dragon {{!}} Institute of Contemporary Arts|website=www.ica.org.uk|access-date=2016-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320115526/https://www.ica.org.uk/whats-on/seasons/ica-and-k11-art-foundation-present-zhang-ding-enter-dragon|archive-date=2016-03-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> showcasing Chinese artists. The foundation also has an art village in Wuhan.<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/> Cheng has been included in the ''[[ArtReview]]'' Power100, ranking 100 in 2014,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artreview.com/power_100/adrian_cheng/|title=Adrian Cheng / Power 100 / Art Review|last=name|first=Site|website=artreview.com|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref> 76 in 2015,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.larryslist.com/artmarket/features/top-10-young-art-collectors/|title=Top 10 Young Art Collectors {{!}} Larry's List - Art Collector Interviews and Art Collector Email Addresses|website=www.larryslist.com|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite web|title = Meet 20 of the World's Most Innovative Art Collectors |url = https://news.artnet.com/people/meet-20-of-the-worlds-most-innovative-art-collectors-117315|website = news.artnet.com|accessdate = 2016-03-16}}</ref> and 46 in 2017.<ref name=CoboSocial1_2017/>\n\n===Recent developments===\nIn 2017, Cheng led the [[Victoria Dockside]] redevelopment on land held by New World since the 1970s, at a cost of $2.6 billion.<ref name=Mingtiandi1_2018>{{cite web |url= https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/projects-real-estate/new-worlds-victoria-dockside-breaks-record-for-kowloon-office-rents/?%20rent-related%20source  |title=  New World\u2019s Victoria Dockside Breaks Record For Kowloon Office Rents |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= Mingtiandi.com }}</ref><ref name=CNN1_2018>{{cite web |url= https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/hong-kong-new-attractions/index.html  |title=  From swanky to retro-cool: 9 exciting attractions coming to Hong Kong |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= CNN }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.skyscrapercenter.com/building/victoria-dockside/9349  |title=  Victoria Dockside |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= Skyscraper Center }}</ref>\n\nCheng presided over the announcement of New World in September 2019 that it would be donating 3 million square feet of agricultural land to the government for public housing and related facilities, to NGOs and to charities to develop social or transitional housing.  Up to a third of the land was to be donated to an affordable social housing project.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1482535-20190925.htm|title=New World donates 3 million square feet of land |newspaper=RTHK|date=25 September 2019|access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Boards and committees==\n\nHe is on the boards of companies such as New World Development, [[Giordano (store)|Giordano]] International, Centennial Success, [[Chow Tai Fook Enterprises]], Broad Park, and New Century Healthcare Holding Company, among others. He is chairman of the China Young Leaders Foundation.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=33378706&privcapId=155731 New World Development - Chi-Kong Cheng], ''[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]]''</ref>\n\n=== Current arts positions===\n* Board Director of the [[National Museum of China]] Foundation<ref name=SCMP1_2015>{{Cite web|title = How New World heir Adrian Cheng combines his passion for art with entrepreneurship|url = http://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/arts-culture/article/1733513/k11-founder-adrian-cheng-bringing-six-exhibitions-art-basel|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref>\n* Director of the [[China Central Academy of Fine Arts|China Central Academy of Fine Arts Museum]] (CAFAM) Funds<ref>{{Cite web|title = articles/Curators in pursuit of the next big thing|url = http://79.125.124.178/articles/Curators-in-pursuit-of-the-next-big-thing/37306|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref>\n* Trustee of [[Royal Academy of Arts]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|title = Art impressario (sic) Cheng brings Monet exhibit to Shanghai - China.org.cn|url = http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2014-04/28/content_32229973.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304060405/http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2014-04/28/content_32229973.htm |archivedate=March 4, 2016 |publisher = [[China Internet Information Center]] |accessdate = 2015-09-30|last = \u5468\u9759}}</ref>\n* Visiting Committee of [[Metropolitan Museum of Art|The Metropolitan Museum of Art]]<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Member of [[Tate|TATE]]\u2019s Asia Pacific Acquisitions Committee<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Member of International Circle of [[Centre Pompidou]]<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Board of directors, [[MoMA PS1]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://momaps1.org/about/board/|title=MoMA PS1: Board of Directors|last=|first=|date=|website=MoMA PS1|publisher=|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref>\n*Board of directors, Public Art Fund<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publicartfund.org/about/board__staff|title=Board & Staff|website=www.publicartfund.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCheng is married to Jennifer Yu.<ref>Joyce Chen, January 24, 2018, [http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=192085&sid=2 Cheng forays into kids' education], ''[[The Standard (Hong Kong)|The Standard]]''</ref> He is known as a collector of [[contemporary art]].<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/>\n\n==Philanthropy ==\nIn April 2020, during the [[Coronavirus disease]] pandemic Cheng revealed announced plans to share millions of surgical face masks free of charge, using 35 specially built vending machines placed in various locations around Hong Kong. He said: \"It is heart-breaking to see so many people suffer because they simply cannot afford or get a hold of masks, which have become so costly and scarce.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/hong-kong-mask-dispensers-scli-intl/index.html|title=A billionaire art collector will distribute 10 million face masks in vending machines around Hong Kong|last=CNN|first=Rob Picheta|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cheng, Adrian}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong billionaires]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong businesspeople]]\n[[Category:New World Development people]]\n[[Category:Non-profit executives]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Taft School alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Election Committee of Hong Kong, 2017\u20132022]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hong Kong businessman}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Adrian Cheng<br />\u912d\u5fd7\u525b\n| birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1979}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hong Kong]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Harvard University]]\n| occupation         = Businessman\n| years_active       = 2000s-present\n| known_for          = Founder of [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] and [[K11 Art Foundation]]\n| title              = Executive Vice-Chairman and General Manager of [[New World Development]]\n| term               = 2015-present\n| awards             = [[Officier de l\u2019Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hongkong.consulfrance.org/Mr-Adrian-Cheng-awarded-insignia-of-Officer-in-the-Order-of-Arts-and-Letters|title=Mr. Adrian Cheng awarded insignia of Officer in the Order of Arts and Letters|last=|first=|date=2017-12-12|website=Consulate general of France in Hong Kong and Macau|access-date=2018-01-03}}</ref><br/>Honorary Doctorate of Humanities degree, [[Savannah College of Art and Design|SCAD]]<br />Honorary Fellowship, [[Lingnan University (Hong Kong)|Lingnan University]]\n|module={{Chinese |child=yes |t=\u912d\u5fd7\u525b|s=\u90d1\u5fd7\u521a|j=zeng6 zi3 gong1|p=Zh\u00e8ng Zh\u00ecg\u0101ng}}\n}}\n'''Adrian Cheng Chi-kong''' ({{zh|t=\u912d\u5fd7\u525b}}, born 1979) is a [[Hong Kong]] businessman.<ref name=NextShark1_2017>{{cite news |last=General |first=Ryan |date=February 20, 2017 |title=Meet the Harvard Graduate Who\u2019s Heir to the World\u2019s Biggest Jewelry Empire |trans-title= |url=https://nextshark.com/adrian-cheng-chow-tai-fook/ |language=English |work=NextShark |location=  |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Reuters1_2013>{{cite news |last=Master |first=Farah |date=May 13, 2013 |title=Adrian Cheng: updating a Hong Kong family empire for a changing China |trans-title= |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-chowtaifook-cheng-idUSBRE94C0ZH20130513 |language=English |work=[[Reuters]] |location=  |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=BusinessofFashion_2017>{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng Launches C Ventures, an \u2018Investment Club\u2019 With Eye on Youth Culture |url = https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/news-bites/adrian-cheng-launches-c-ventures-an-investment-club-with-eye-on-youth-culture |website = Business of Fashion}}</ref> He is the executive vice-chairman and general manager of the Hong Kong-listed [[New World Development]],<ref name=NWD_2015>{{Cite web|title = Corporate {{!}} New World Development Company Limited Official Website|url = http://www.nwd.com.hk/corporate|website = www.nwd.com.hk|accessdate = 8 October 2015}}</ref> executive director of jewellery company [[Chow Tai Fook]], and founder of the [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] brand.<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\">{{Cite web|url=http://corporate.chowtaifook.com/en/about/board.php|title=About Us > Board of Directors {{!}} Chow Tai Fook Jewellery Group Limited|website=corporate.chowtaifook.com|access-date=2016-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520145306/http://corporate.chowtaifook.com/en/about/board.php|archive-date=2016-05-20|url-status=dead|df=}}</ref><ref name=SCMP1_2015/><ref name=AsiaTatler1_2018>{{Cite web|title = 5 Things To Know About Victoria Dockside |url = https://hk.asiatatler.com/life/5-things-to-know-about-victoria-dockside |website = Asia Tatler}}</ref> Cheng has been on the [[40 under 40 (Fortune magazine)|40 under 40 list by ''Fortune'']], and in 2017, he was awarded the [[Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]].<ref name=CoboSocial1_2017>{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng Awarded Officier de L\u2019Ordre des Arts et des Lettres |url = https://www.cobosocial.com/dossiers/adrian-cheng-awarded-officier-de-lordre-des-arts-et-des-lettres/ |website = Cobosocial}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nCheng was born in 1979.<ref name=Reuters1_2013/> He is the oldest child of [[Henry Cheng]],<ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> and among his siblings are businesswoman Sonia Cheng<ref name=AsiaTatler1_2018/> and Brian Cheng.<ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> Cheng is the designated heir to his grandfather [[Cheng Yu-tung]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Adrian Cheng moves up after K11 artistry - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=11&art_id=154796&sid=43996793&con_type=1&d_str=20150303&fc=2|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150908231034/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=11|archive-date = 2015-09-08|url-status=dead|df = }}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Adrian Chi-Kong Cheng {{!}} #BoF500 {{!}} The Business of Fashion|url = http://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/adrian-chi-kong-cheng|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref> a multi-billionaire<ref name=Coconuts1_2016>[http://hongkong.coconuts.co/2016/09/30/hong-kong-billionaire-tycoon-cheng-yu-tung-dies-aged-91 Hong Kong billionaire tycoon Cheng Yu-tung dies aged 91], Coconuts, 30 September 2016</ref> known for founding [[New World Development]] and [[Chow Tai Fook Enterprises]],<ref name=NextShark1_2017/><ref name=Reuters1_2013/><ref name=BusinessofFashion_2017/> both Cheng family holdings.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|title = Still in Control, Hong Kong Property Tycoons Face a Younger Generation|url = https://www.cnbc.com/id/44899567|accessdate = 2015-09-30|first = Alex Frew McMillan{{!}}CNBC|last = Contributor}}</ref> Cheng majored in East Asian studies at [[Harvard University]] and graduated with a Bachelor of Arts degree.  Cheng's father had established the New World Harvard Kennedy School Fellows Programme in an agreement with Harvard in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www4.hku.hk/hongrads/index.php/archive/graduate_detail/314|title=Honorary Degrees Congregation|website=University of Hong Kong|access-date=6 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=New World Group and the State Administration of Foreign Experts Affairs renewed the agreement for \"New World Harvard Kennedy School Fellows Programme\"|url=https://www.nwd.com.hk/content/new-world-group-and-state-administration-foreign-experts-affairs-renewed-agreement-new-world|website=New World Development Co. Ltd|access-date=6 February 2019}}</ref>  Cheng later went to [[Japan]] to study [[Japanese culture]] for a year.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Business career ==\n=== UBS and Chow Tai Fook ===\nEarly in his career, Cheng was a banker at [[Goldman Sachs]] and [[UBS]].<ref name=Reuters1_2013/> Following a two-year stint at UBS AG,<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" /> in 2006,<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/> Cheng joined the family business,<ref name=\":3\" /> the private Chow Tai Fook Holdings empire.<ref name=\":0\" /> He became executive director of the listed<ref name=\":3\"/> Chow Tai Fook<ref name=SCMP1_2015/> Jewelry Group.<ref name=\"corporate.chowtaifook.com\"/>\n\n===New World Development===\nIn March 2007, Cheng became the executive director<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/> and a board member at New World Development,<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013/> a Hong Kong-listed company<ref name=NWD_2015/> which is the biggest part of Chow Tai Fook Holdings.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=FinancialTimes1_2013>{{Cite news|title = Adrian Cheng adds shine to Chow Tai Fook brand|url = http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/424863ca-d33a-11e2-95d4-00144feab7de.html#slide0|newspaper = Financial Times|date = 2013-10-08|access-date = 2015-09-30|issn = 0307-1766|first = Paul J.|last = Davies}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Brave new world as Cheng retires - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?art_id=120262&con_type=1|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Reflections of Siem - The Standard|url = http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?art_id=143664&con_type=3|website = www.thestandard.com.hk|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = New World founder makes way for son at top of developer|url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/29/newworld-management-idUSL4E8DT2EL20120229|newspaper = Reuters|date = 2012-02-29|access-date = 2015-09-30}}</ref> In 2012, he became joint [[general manager]] of New World Development<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/> and he also became executive vice-chairman in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nwd.com.hk/content/adrian-cheng-promoted-nwd-executive-vice-chairman|title=Home {{!}} New World Development Company Limited Official Website|website=www.nwd.com.hk|access-date=2016-05-17}}</ref>\n\n===K11 brand===\nCheng introduced the concept of \"museum-retail\"<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/f5dc36ee-5851-11e4-a31b-00144feab7de.html|title=Arts interview: Adrian Cheng|last=Harris|first=Gareth|date=2014-10-24|newspaper=Financial Times|issn=0307-1766|access-date=2016-05-17}}</ref> by founding the [[K11 (Hong Kong)|K11]] brand in 2008. Cheng's first K11 museum-retail mall opened in [[Tsim Sha Tsui]] (Hong Kong) in 2009, and later a branch was opened in [[K11 (Shanghai)|Shanghai]]. K11 museum-retail shopping centers currently have branches in [[Guangzhou]], Hong Kong, Shanghai, [[Shenyang]], and [[Wuhan]].<ref name=Mingtiandi1_2018/><ref name=CNN1_2018/>\n\n===K11 Art Foundation===\nHe founded the [[K11 Art Foundation]] (KAF) in 2010, a vehicle for art promotion within the malls, serving as a platform for Chinese artists and their works.<ref>{{Cite web|title = The Foundation - K11 Art Foundation|url = http://www.k11artfoundation.org/en/about-us/|accessdate = 2015-09-09}}</ref>  He initiated collaborations between the foundation and international museums and art institutions such as [[Palais de Tokyo]] in [[Paris]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.artnet.com/art-world/k11-art-foundations-chinese-french-connection-at-fiac-143086|title=K11 Art Foundation's Chinese-French Connection at FIAC - artnet News|website=artnet News|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref> and [[Institute of Contemporary Arts]] (ICA) in London,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ica.org.uk/whats-on/seasons/ica-and-k11-art-foundation-present-zhang-ding-enter-dragon|title=ICA and K11 Art Foundation present Zhang Ding: Enter the Dragon {{!}} Institute of Contemporary Arts|website=www.ica.org.uk|access-date=2016-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320115526/https://www.ica.org.uk/whats-on/seasons/ica-and-k11-art-foundation-present-zhang-ding-enter-dragon|archive-date=2016-03-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> showcasing Chinese artists. The foundation also has an art village in Wuhan.<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/> Cheng has been included in the ''[[ArtReview]]'' Power100, ranking 100 in 2014,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artreview.com/power_100/adrian_cheng/|title=Adrian Cheng / Power 100 / Art Review|last=name|first=Site|website=artreview.com|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref> 76 in 2015,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.larryslist.com/artmarket/features/top-10-young-art-collectors/|title=Top 10 Young Art Collectors {{!}} Larry's List - Art Collector Interviews and Art Collector Email Addresses|website=www.larryslist.com|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite web|title = Meet 20 of the World's Most Innovative Art Collectors |url = https://news.artnet.com/people/meet-20-of-the-worlds-most-innovative-art-collectors-117315|website = news.artnet.com|accessdate = 2016-03-16}}</ref> and 46 in 2017.<ref name=CoboSocial1_2017/>\n\n===Recent developments===\nIn 2017, Cheng led the [[Victoria Dockside]] redevelopment on land held by New World since the 1970s, at a cost of $2.6 billion.<ref name=Mingtiandi1_2018>{{cite web |url= https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/projects-real-estate/new-worlds-victoria-dockside-breaks-record-for-kowloon-office-rents/?%20rent-related%20source  |title=  New World\u2019s Victoria Dockside Breaks Record For Kowloon Office Rents |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= Mingtiandi.com }}</ref><ref name=CNN1_2018>{{cite web |url= https://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/hong-kong-new-attractions/index.html  |title=  From swanky to retro-cool: 9 exciting attractions coming to Hong Kong |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= CNN }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.skyscrapercenter.com/building/victoria-dockside/9349  |title=  Victoria Dockside |accessdate=June 25, 2018|publisher= Skyscraper Center }}</ref>\n\nCheng presided over the announcement of New World in September 2019 that it would be donating 3 million square feet of agricultural land to the government for public housing and related facilities, to NGOs and to charities to develop social or transitional housing.  Up to a third of the land was to be donated to an affordable social housing project.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1482535-20190925.htm|title=New World donates 3 million square feet of land |newspaper=RTHK|date=25 September 2019|access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Boards and committees==\n\nHe is on the boards of companies such as New World Development, [[Giordano (store)|Giordano]] International, Centennial Success, [[Chow Tai Fook Enterprises]], Broad Park, and New Century Healthcare Holding Company, among others. He is chairman of the China Young Leaders Foundation.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=33378706&privcapId=155731 New World Development - Chi-Kong Cheng], ''[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]]''</ref>\n\n=== Current arts positions===\n* Board Director of the [[National Museum of China]] Foundation<ref name=SCMP1_2015>{{Cite web|title = How New World heir Adrian Cheng combines his passion for art with entrepreneurship|url = http://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/arts-culture/article/1733513/k11-founder-adrian-cheng-bringing-six-exhibitions-art-basel|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref>\n* Director of the [[China Central Academy of Fine Arts|China Central Academy of Fine Arts Museum]] (CAFAM) Funds<ref>{{Cite web|title = articles/Curators in pursuit of the next big thing|url = http://79.125.124.178/articles/Curators-in-pursuit-of-the-next-big-thing/37306|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref>\n* Trustee of [[Royal Academy of Arts]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|title = Art impressario (sic) Cheng brings Monet exhibit to Shanghai - China.org.cn|url = http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2014-04/28/content_32229973.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304060405/http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2014-04/28/content_32229973.htm |archivedate=March 4, 2016 |publisher = [[China Internet Information Center]] |accessdate = 2015-09-30|last = \u5468\u9759}}</ref>\n* Visiting Committee of [[Metropolitan Museum of Art|The Metropolitan Museum of Art]]<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Member of [[Tate|TATE]]\u2019s Asia Pacific Acquisitions Committee<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Member of International Circle of [[Centre Pompidou]]<ref name=\":4\" />\n* Board of directors, [[MoMA PS1]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://momaps1.org/about/board/|title=MoMA PS1: Board of Directors|last=|first=|date=|website=MoMA PS1|publisher=|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref>\n*Board of directors, Public Art Fund<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publicartfund.org/about/board__staff|title=Board & Staff|website=www.publicartfund.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCheng is married to Jennifer Yu.<ref>Joyce Chen, January 24, 2018, [http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=192085&sid=2 Cheng forays into kids' education], ''[[The Standard (Hong Kong)|The Standard]]''</ref> He is known as a collector of [[contemporary art]].<ref name=FinancialTimes2_2014/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cheng, Adrian}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong billionaires]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong businesspeople]]\n[[Category:New World Development people]]\n[[Category:Non-profit executives]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Taft School alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Election Committee of Hong Kong, 2017\u20132022]]\n", "name_user": "PatrickSmithUSA", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adrian_Cheng"}
